OL,3,CEx-footballer Paul Ince banned from
OL,4,Croads after admitting drink-driving
OL,6,FMr Rogers said Ince had been at
OL,7,FHeswall Golf Club for a competition
OL,8,Fand had not eaten before having two
OL,9,Fdrinks in the clubhouse.
OL,11,FHe said: "He felt fine to drive, of
OL,12,Fcourse we now know that he shouldn't
OL,13,Fhave done."
OL,15,FHe said that as he was driving home,
OL,16,FInce approached a roundabout at about
OL,17,F20mph when his phone slipped and he
OL,18,Finstinctively reached for it and
OL,19,Fveered the car, clipping the kerb.
