OL,3,CEx-footballer Paul Ince banned from
OL,4,Croads after admitting drink-driving
OL,6,FHe is a frequent visitor and supporter
OL,7,Fto the Future Youth Zone charity in
OL,8,FDagenham, where he grew up, and also
OL,9,Fsupports Claire House Children's
OL,10,FHospice in Wirral, he said.
OL,12,FMr Rogers outlined Ince's playing
OL,13,Fcareer and said he then went into
OL,14,Fmanagement. He added: "He now does a
OL,15,Flimited amount of media work and
OL,16,Fcharity work."
OL,18,FHe said Ince, of Quarry Road, Neston,
OL,19,Fwished to apologise to the court.
